Boil a large #pot of salted water for the @dried linguine{180%g}. When the water is boiling, add the linguine then bring back to the boil. Cook until softened, ~{10-12%mins}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander and pop back in the pot, off the heat. Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, clean and roughly chop the @mushrooms{250%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press).

Place a large pan over medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, fry the @chorizo{100%g} until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%mins}.

Add the mushrooms and garlic to the #pan (with a drizzle of oil if needed). Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Fry until browned, ~{6-8%mins}.

Stir in the @sun dried tomato paste{2%sachets} and @creme fraiche{110%g}. Loosen with a splash of @water{to taste} if you feel it's too thick. Add the pasta and @grated Italian style hard cheese{2%units} and stir well to coat and cook for ~{1-2%mins}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide your creamy chorizo pasta between #bowls{}. Garnish with a sprinkling of cheese.